
The following are major news items in
leading Turkish newspapers on Sunday.
TURKIYE (Turkey):
-- Egyptian Minister of Foreign Trade and Industry Rachid Mohamed
Rachid told the Turkiye daily published on Sunday that Turkey and
Egypt were not rivals but partners, calling on Turkish
businessmen to invest in his country.
YENI SAFAK (New Dawn):
-- Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan met with rectors
of universities in Istanbul on Saturday and said departments of
Kurdish language and literature would be opened at many
universities soon.
CUMHURIYET (Republic):
-- Turkish Labor and Social Security Minister Omer Dincer said
Saturday that 16.5 million working people in Turkey were
receiving salaries below the poverty line.
